  "implementation_notes": [
    "RTL: Use dir='rtl' on the <html> or wrapper element. Logical CSS properties handle mirror automatically.",
    "Filled state: The browser manages filled vs placeholder text display natively via <input> and ::placeholder.",
    "Focused state: Implemented via :focus-within on .text-input__field. Border becomes transparent; ::after shows 2px underline.",
    "Pressed underline width: Figma uses fixed 112px on a 320px component (35%). Responsive implementation uses 50% approximation.",
    "Error state on disabled: Disabled takes visual priority. .text-input--disabled overrides .text-input--error border.",
    "Assembly: text-input is a standalone base. Compose with input-affix for prefix/suffix icons. Compose with form-field for error messages."
  ]
